The paper focuses on improving the performance of mobile edge computing (MEC) in small cell networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm is based on game theory, specifically a potential game, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the game theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The algorithm involves joint offloading decision and resource allocation, which are topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and system and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the computation complexity and price of anarchy, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT).
